(iStock) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories &nbsp;Beni = The head of a Democratic Republic of Congo army operation against rebels in the country's east says it has freed 26 people held by a Uganda-based rebel group.Captain Mak Hazukay Mongba said on Wednesday the army has freed the hostages over the past several days.Some of the freed hostages said the rebels of the Allied Democratic Forces want DRC's army to recognise they control parts of Beni.Omar Kavota, director of a local rights group, said the rebel group presents a regional threat because it aims to take control in Uganda.The ADF rebels are among scores of armed groups vying for control in mineral-rich eastern Congo and are blamed for killing nearly 700 civilians since October 2014.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.